@bolkedebruin Based on Sqlalchemy documentation (http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/core/type_basics.html):

`PickleType builds upon the Binary type to apply Python’s pickle.dumps()` and `impl alias of LargeBinary`. 

Sqlalchemy should have same underlying implementation on a specific DB for both PickleType and LargeBinary. I think it should be compilable on Postgres.

I just realized the change in the semantics of this PR. We don't want dagruns to end prematurely, but that doesn't mean we want to run tasks that have skipped dependencies (intuitively you would expect to skip any task that has dependencies that weren't run by default, i.e. the trigger rule is called ALL_SUCCESS and skipped tasks are not successful ones, and that was also the old behavior in 1.7.3).

This is going to break some use cases which could be alright, but I feel these new semantics make less sense than before so it's a bad reason to break existing use cases.

I will get started on a PR for a new ALL_SUCCESS_NOT_SKIPPED trigger rule but again I feel this is hacky and really we should have the old ALL_SUCCESS (default) and a new ALL_SUCCESS_OR_SKIPPED trigger rule if desired.

@bolkedebruin @dhuang 

@mistercrunch

Yeah, agreed that changing behavior of `ALL_SUCCESS` to fix propagation behavior was a bad call. Sorry for the trouble!

As far as I can tell, BranchPython, ShortCircuit, and LatestOnly operators all only set their **direct** downstream tasks as `SKIPPED` (https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/blob/1.8.0/airflow/operators/python_operator.py#L109). So the states of any task past that is determined by the trigger rule logic. Agreed it sounds like logic should be handled in the scheduler, but it probably still to has be defined somehow by the operator? For example, I assume all tasks downstream from `LatestOnly` should be skipped despite any `ALL_SUCCESS` trigger rule. But tasks downstream from a `Sensor` with `soft_fail=True`...should fail if it has an `ALL_SUCCESS` trigger rule, I think?

@aoen I filed https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AIRFLOW-983 a few days ago if you need a ticket for the better fix
